## Complete verification form

To verify your business, you must complete a verification form with information about your business, primary or legal representative, and designated point of contact. To complete the form, go to the Developer Portal and complete the following steps:

**Note**: Only registered organization admins can view the Business page and complete verification.

1.  Find **My organizations** and select your desired organization.

![](https://sf16-sg.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tiktok-open-platform-sg/ttop_doc_images/69b9e19b8294b9e6c8b72d1b595f61bc)

1.  Go to the **Business** page then click the **Start verification** button**.**
2.  Fill out all sections of the verification form and upload certification documents.

1.  Business details: upload certification
2.  Primary representative: upload certification
3.  Operational representative: register and verify an email address

4.  Submit the verification form for review. You can expect to hear back in 1-3 business days.

**Note**: If you're unable to find the entry point for business verification on your organization's Overview page, you may need to first connect an app with the mini game app type. Follow the steps below.

If connecting an app to your organization for the first time, you can follow this flow:

1.  On the Developer Portal, click **Manage apps**.
2.  Click the **Connect an app** button if you're creating a mini game for the first time.
3.  Select **Organization** as the ownership type.

![](https://sf16-sg.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tiktok-open-platform-sg/ttop_doc_images/f7e5f397f59cb8a15a2476a51107a243)

1.  Enter the name of your mini game, then select **Mini game** as the app type.

![](https://sf16-sg.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tiktok-open-platform-sg/ttop_doc_images/7111e8ef7b8cae8b3eef70f7e75df861)

1.  Go to the Developer Portal, then click **My organizations**. Click your organization. You should see the business verification card on the **Overview** page.

